.TH AGENT-HOOK-PRE-EDIT 1 "2026-06-30" "agentguard" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
agent-hook-pre-edit \- guard agent file edits before they are applied
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B agent-hook-pre-edit
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B agent-hook-pre-edit
reads an agent edit hook JSON payload from standard input, extracts target
paths, blocks edits to secret-like files, tracks repeated edit churn, and
reminds the agent to apply the loaded design, workflow, code-style, and
language-specific rule fragments before changing code or configuration.
.PP
The churn guard warns at
.B AGENTGUARD_EDIT_CHURN_WARN
edits to one file and blocks at
.B AGENTGUARD_EDIT_CHURN_BLOCK .
Set
.B AGENTGUARD_EDIT_CHURN_BYPASS=1
for a deliberate repeated-edit pass.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The edit is allowed, possibly with warnings or reminders.
.TP
.B 2
The edit is blocked.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR agent-hook-post-edit (1)
